__Issue__:

__Tag__:

__Summary__:--incremental work well in condition of --keep-packs

__Precondition__

1. Tested Pkgs:
2. Tested Repo: https://download.tizendev.org/snapshots/trunk/common/latest
3. Tested Conf: conf_fixtures/tizendev.cfg

__Steps__

> if [ -d ~/GBS-ROOT/local/repos ];then sudo rm ~/GBS-ROOT/local/repos -rf; fi

> if [ -d ~/GBS-ROOT/local/scratch.i586.0 ];then sudo rm ~/GBS-ROOT/local/scratch.i586.0 -rf; fi

> if [ -d ./build ];then rm build -rf; fi

> mkdir build

> cd build

> ../tools/create_proj ../specs/fake.spec

> ../tools/create_proj ../specs/sw-tools.spec

> gbs -c ../conf_fixtures/tizendev.cfg build sw-tools -A i586

> test -n "`find ~/GBS-ROOT/local/repos -name "*sw-tools*.rpm"`"

#libpython is only depanded by sw-tools but not fake
> sudo chroot ~/GBS-ROOT/local/scratch.i586.0/ rpm -qa|grep 'libpython'

> gbs -c ../conf_fixtures/tizendev.cfg build fake -A i586 --keep-packs --incremental --overwrite

#check source package whether changed or not
> cd fake && test -n "`git status | grep "working directory clean"`" && cd ..

> cd sw-tools && test -n "`git status | grep "working directory clean"`" && cd ..

#--incremental force to clear buildroot even there is --keep-packs
> (! sudo chroot ~/GBS-ROOT/local/scratch.i586.0/ rpm -qa|grep 'libpython')
